House Bill 619 (AS PASSED HOUSE AND SENATE)
By: Representative Greene of the 154th
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend an Act providing a new charter for the City of Donalsonville, approved April 29,
2 1997 (Ga. L. 1997, p. 4524), as amended, so as to revise the election schedule for the mayor
3 so as to better stagger elections of the mayor and councilmembers; to provide for an interim
4 term of office; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other
5 purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 An Act providing a new charter for the City of Donalsonville, approved April 29, 1997 (Ga.
9 L. 1997, p. 4524), as amended, is amended by revising Section 2.11 as follows:
10 "SECTION 2.11.
11 Terms and qualifications for office.
12 Except as provided for in Section 5.12, the mayor and each member of the council shall serve
13 for terms of four years and until their respective successors are elected and qualified. No
14 person shall be eligible to serve as mayor or councilmember unless he or she shall have been
