15 a resident of the city for a period of at least 12 months immediately prior to the date of the
16 election of the mayor or members of the council; each shall continue to reside therein during
17 his or her period of service and to be registered and qualified to vote in municipal elections
18 of this city."
19 SECTION 2.
20 Said Act is further amended by revising Section 5.12 as follows:
21 "SECTION 5.12.
22 Regular elections; time for holding.
23 (a) The mayor and council shall cause an election to be held at the city hall or such other
24 place in the city as the mayor and council shall direct and designate. All general municipal
25 elections shall be held on the Tuesday next following the first Monday in November, 2025,
26 and on such day biennially thereafter. Except as provided for in subsection (b) of this
27 section, each elected officer shall serve for a term of four years and until a successor is
28 elected and qualified, such term beginning on January 1 of the year following the officer's
29 election.
30 (b) At the municipal general election held in November, 2025, there shall be elected a
31 mayor who shall serve a two year term of office and until a successor is elected and
32 qualified. The successor to such mayor shall be elected at the municipal general election
33 held in November, 2027, and shall serve a four year term of office until a successor is
34 elected an qualified. Thereafter the mayor shall be elected as provided for by
35 subsection (a) of this section.
36 (c) Notwithstanding any provision of this Act, no term of office to which a person has
37 been elected prior to the effective date of this Act shall be shortened or lengthened except
38 pursuant to the procedures established by state law."
